
Module Name:
Crop Prediction

Objective:
The objective of this module is to recommend the most suitable crop based on soil nutrients and environmental conditions.

Description:
Crop Prediction is the final phase of the project. It uses the trained model and input parameters to predict the most appropriate crop for cultivation.

Input Parameters:
1. Nitrogen (N)
2. Phosphorus (P)
3. Potassium (K)
4. Temperature
5. Humidity
6. pH Value
7. Rainfall

Methodology:

Step 1:
Collect soil and environmental parameters from the user.

Step 2:
Process the input data.

Step 3:
Pass the input values to the prediction module.

Step 4:
Analyze the input parameters.

Step 5:
Predict the most suitable crop.

Step 6:
Display the recommended crop to the user.

Tools and Technologies Used:
• Python
• Pandas
• NumPy
• Scikit-Learn
• Jupyter Notebook

Input:
Soil nutrient values and environmental conditions.

Output:
Recommended Crop

Advantages:
• Supports smart farming.
• Provides quick crop recommendations.
• Easy to use.
• Helps improve agricultural productivity.

Applications:
• Precision Agriculture
• Smart Farming Systems
• Agricultural Decision Support Systems

Conclusion:
The Crop Prediction module successfully recommends suitable crops based on soil and environmental conditions. This helps farmers make informed decisions and improve crop yield.
